headline: Assessing AutoZone Shares After Latest 4.8% Drop and Five-Year Surge of 240%
summary: Thinking about what to do with AutoZone stock? You are not alone. Whether you already own shares or are eyeing that ticker for your portfolio, AutoZone’s recent price swings have a lot of investors leaning forward. After years of steady gains, the stock cooled off a bit in the past month, dropping about 4.8%. Still, zoom out and the long-term performance is clear: up over 240% in five years and more than 75% in the last three. Even the dip this month has not erased year-to-date gains, which...
